Column.name: Note
Column.value:
Infrastructure Device Pattern
  • Infrastructure Device Elements are used to represent physical devices such as physical servers, telecom equipment, and other devices.
  • Please note, Storage, Appliances and Network devices have their own elements to use.
  • This Element's Stereotype extends the UML Device element.
Element Information
  1. Stereotype = Infrastructure Device
  2. Tag Type = Describes main purpose of the Device. For example, "server" type would be used for an IBM Power server.
  3. Tag Summary = A Structured Tag that describes the Appliance's Vendor and Version. If version is unknown, leave it blank or put a period.
Constraints
  • This element is NOT used for Network Devices, Storage Devices, or VM's.
Examples
  • IBM Power Server
  • Avaya Telecom Physical Equipment
